# Dual-region deployment (Creator Vault)

Every release must work **both internationally and in mainland China** without VPN.

## Code requirements

- **No** Google Fonts, Unsplash, or other blocked foreign CDNs. Use `src/lib/assets.ts` for local paths (`public/covers/`, `#tip/...`).
- New images/fonts → add under `public/`, reference via `import.meta.env.BASE_URL`.
- Vercel build: `npm run build` (base `/`). China build: `npm run build:china` (base `./`).

## Deploy targets

| Region | Host | URL |
|--------|------|-----|
| International | Vercel (linked to `main`) | `https://<project>.vercel.app` |
| China / domestic | GitHub Pages (`gh-pages` branch) | `https://zxc6778.github.io/creator-vault/` |

**Never** use `cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/...` for HTML — it serves pages as plain text (looks like raw code).

## After code changes

1. Push to `main` → Vercel redeploys automatically.
2. Run `npm run deploy:china` to update GitHub Pages (`gh-pages`), **or** enable GitHub Action: copy `scripts/github-workflow-deploy-dual.yml` → `.github/workflows/deploy-dual.yml` on github.com.
3. Verify both URLs load the wallet UI (not source code).

## Gitee (optional)

`npm run build:gitee` for `https://<user>.gitee.io/creator-vault/` if user mirrors to Gitee.
